<DOC><DOCNO> AP891204-0233 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-04-89 1005EST</FILEID><FIRST>a a BC-SPE--Travel:Hideaway     12-04 0146</FIRST><SECOND>BC-SPE--Travel: Hideaway,0148</SECOND><HEAD>SPECIAL EDITION</HEAD><HEAD>Travel: Hideaway</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   The Boulders, in Carefree, Ariz., has been chosen the top U.S.resort for the third consecutive year in a survey by HideawayReport, a monthly travel newsletter for affluent business travelers.   New to the 1989 list of top resorts picked by the sampling of2,500 subscribers to the newsletter was Halekulani in Hawaii, whichwas 11th.   Other top resorts in the survey, in order: The Greenbrier, WestVirginia; Ritz-Carlton Laguna Niguel, California; Ritz-CarltonNaples, Florida; Manua Lani Bay, Hawaii; Mauna Kea, Hawaii; TheCloisters, Georgia; Ventana, California; Auberge de Soleil,California; and the Lodge at Pebble Beach, California.   More than 70 percent of the subscribers to Hideaway Report,which marks its 10th anniversary this year, are corporatepresidents or chief executive officers with a median annual incomeof $280,000. Reader average age is 49.</TEXT></DOC>